Community Edition (CE) Terms
============================

Kitakod Ventures grants a right to use all features of the r8r
Community Edition for free, subject to the following conditions:

PERMITTED:
- Internal use within your organization without restrictions
- Use in production for your own workloads
- Modification for internal use
- Contributing improvements back to the project

NOT PERMITTED without a commercial license:
- Selling, reselling, or offering r8r as a managed/hosted service
- Re-exposing r8r features or API to third-party end users as a service
- Bundling r8r into a commercial product for redistribution
- Removing or altering license/copyright notices

Source Code
===========

The source code compiled without the "enterprise" feature flag is
open source under the AGPLv3 license terms and conditions. See
LICENSE-AGPL for the full license text.

The source code compiled with the "enterprise" feature flag, or any
code that performs license key validation, is proprietary and requires
a commercial license from Kitakod Ventures.

